The paper deals with formal verification of incentive properties in mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). The use of computer-aided verification techniques suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves logical reasoning and proof techniques, which are relevant to the subfield of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The use of randomness in the mechanism design suggests a connection to the subfield of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of complex systems, which is relevant to the subfield of computational complexity (cs.CC).
